8. Risk Metrics: Maximum Drawdown¶

In [30]:
# Calculate cumulative returns and drawdown
df['Cumulative'] = (1 + df['Close'].pct_change()).cumprod()
peak = df['Cumulative'].cummax()
drawdown = (df['Cumulative'] - peak) / peak * 100

# Area chart
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
plt.fill_between(df.index, drawdown, color='red', alpha=0.3)
plt.title('Maximum Drawdown (%)')
plt.xlabel('Date')
plt.ylabel('Drawdown (%)')
plt.grid(True)
plt.savefig("risk metrics.png")
plt.show()

12. Predictive Modeling (ARIMA Example)¶

In [48]:
# Step 1: Reset index (if needed)
df = df.reset_index()

# Step 2: Rename column (if needed)
# df = df.rename(columns={'your_date_column': 'Date'})

# Step 3: Convert to datetime
df['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['Date'], utc=True)
df['Date'] = df['Date'].dt.tz_localize(None)

# Step 4: Set index with frequency
df = df.set_index('Date').asfreq('D')

# Step 5: Fit ARIMA model
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
model = ARIMA(df['Close'], order=(5, 1, 0))
results = model.fit()

# Step 6: Forecast and plot
forecast = results.get_forecast(steps=30)
forecast_index = pd.date_range(df.index[-1], periods=30, freq='D')

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
plt.plot(df.index, df['Close'], label='Historical')
plt.plot(forecast_index, forecast.predicted_mean, label='Forecast', linestyle='--')
plt.title('30-Day Price Forecast (ARIMA)')
plt.legend()
plt.savefig("modeling.png")
plt.show()

13. Sharpe Ratio¶

In [60]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

# Calculate daily returns
daily_returns = df['Close'].pct_change(fill_method=None).dropna()

# Annualized Sharpe Ratio
risk_free_rate = 0.05 / 252  # Example: 5% annual risk-free rate
sharpe = (daily_returns.mean() - risk_free_rate) / daily_returns.std() * np.sqrt(252)

# Plot 1: Distribution of Daily Returns (Histogram)
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
plt.hist(daily_returns, bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')
plt.axvline(daily_returns.mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean Daily Return')
plt.title('Distribution of eBay Daily Returns')
plt.xlabel('Daily Returns')
plt.ylabel('Frequency')
plt.legend()
plt.savefig("sjape ratio.png")
plt.show()

# Plot 2: Cumulative Returns vs. Risk-Free Rate
cumulative_returns = (1 + daily_returns).cumprod()
cumulative_risk_free = (1 + risk_free_rate) ** np.arange(len(daily_returns))

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
plt.plot(cumulative_returns.index, cumulative_returns, label='eBay Cumulative Returns', color='green')
plt.plot(cumulative_returns.index, cumulative_risk_free, label='Risk-Free Asset', color='red', linestyle='--')
plt.title('Cumulative Returns: eBay vs. Risk-Free Asset')
plt.xlabel('Date')
plt.ylabel('Cumulative Returns')
plt.legend()
plt.savefig("ration shape.png")
plt.show()

# Print Sharpe Ratio
print(f'Sharpe Ratio: {sharpe:.2f}')

Sharpe Ratio: 0.48

15. Trading Strategy Backtest (Moving Average Crossover)¶

In [57]:
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data and handle datetime
df = pd.read_csv("ebay_stocks_data.csv")
df['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['Date'], utc=True)
df.set_index('Date', inplace=True)

# Calculate moving averages
df['50D_MA'] = df['Close'].rolling(50).mean()
df['200D_MA'] = df['Close'].rolling(200).mean()

# Generate signals using boolean masking (avoid positional slicing)
df['Signal'] = 0  # Initialize column
mask = df.index >= df.index[50]  # Rows from the 50th position onwards
df.loc[mask, 'Signal'] = np.where(
    df.loc[mask, '50D_MA'] > df.loc[mask, '200D_MA'], 1, -1
)

# Calculate position changes and strategy returns
df['Position'] = df['Signal'].diff()
df['Strategy Returns'] = df['Close'].pct_change() * df['Signal'].shift(1)
df['Cumulative Strategy Returns'] = (1 + df['Strategy Returns']).cumprod()
df['Cumulative Buy/Hold Returns'] = (1 + df['Close'].pct_change()).cumprod()

# Plotting and metrics (unchanged)
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 8))
plt.subplot(2, 1, 1)
plt.plot(df.index, df['Close'], label='Close Price', color='blue', alpha=0.5)
plt.plot(df.index, df['50D_MA'], label='50D MA', color='orange')
plt.plot(df.index, df['200D_MA'], label='200D MA', color='red')
plt.scatter(df[df['Position'] == 2].index, df[df['Position'] == 2]['Close'], 
           marker='^', color='green', s=100, label='Buy Signal')
plt.scatter(df[df['Position'] == -2].index, df[df['Position'] == -2]['Close'], 
           marker='v', color='red', s=100, label='Sell Signal')
plt.title('eBay Stock Price with Moving Average Crossover Signals')
plt.ylabel('Price (USD)')
plt.legend()

plt.subplot(2, 1, 2)
plt.plot(df.index, df['Cumulative Strategy Returns'], label='Strategy Returns', color='purple')
plt.plot(df.index, df['Cumulative Buy/Hold Returns'], label='Buy/Hold Returns', color='gray')
plt.title('Cumulative Returns: Strategy vs. Buy/Hold')
plt.xlabel('Date')
plt.ylabel('Cumulative Returns')
plt.legend()

plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig("stock price.png")
plt.show()
